    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-05T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-05T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 5, 1941—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. For Murphy. In view of the contents of Vichy’s two telegrams of June 4
                    regarding Monick’s conversation at the Embassy,<note n="99" xml:id="d307fn99"
                        >See telegrams Nos. 626 and 627, from the Ambassador in France, <ref
                            target="#pg_361">pp. 361</ref> and <ref target="#pg_362">362</ref>,
                        respectively.</note> you should suspend all action on Department’s telegram
                    no. 125, June 4, 6 p.m., pending further instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
